:decimal;"><li style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Peace in Gotham City</em>: =
On Saturday afternoon, MSG Networks and Altice USA finally announced a truc=
e, and the cable operator will resume carrying the regional sports networks=
 MSG and MSG+ on its Optimum systems. The deal ends a two-month blackout of=
 local Knicks, Rangers, and Islanders games and keeps MSG in the forlorn re=
gional sports business=E2=80=94at least for now. Ultimately, however, MSG c=
onvinced Optimum to use a <em>glide path</em> strategy, including the
R.S.N.s in its =E2=80=9CEverything TV=E2=80=9D digital package for new subs=
cribers.<br/><br/>As part of the deal, however, Optimum will reportedly low=
er its carriage fee from $10 per subscriber per month to $8=E2=80=94a nice =
reciprocal <em>grinfucking </em>maneuver to save face. The agreement will e=
ffectively reduce Altice=E2=80=99s payments to MSG from $125 million per ye=
ar to about $96 million, according to a note from Guggenheim. =E2=80=9CWe u=
nderstand the negative reaction today, as investors have expressed they wou=
ld like [MSG
Networks] to walk away from the R.S.N. business, and today=E2=80=99s announ=
cement makes that slightly less likely,=E2=80=9D the note continued. Guggen=
heim also predicted that MSG=E2=80=99s teams =E2=80=9Cwill likely agree to =
a haircut on their local media rights=E2=80=9D because the R.S.N. business =
is so untenable at the moment.</li><li style=3D"Margin:0 0 24px 0;"><em>Reg=
arding that Big East-ACC merger talk</em>: Recently, <strong>Mike Krzyzewsk=
i</strong> mused on his SiriusXM show about a merger between the Big East a=
nd ACC,
envisioning a college basketball behemoth replete with big brands and histo=
ric programs that could compete with the football-heavy Big Ten and SEC. =
=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99d like to see something innovative,=E2=80=9D Coach K sai=
d. =E2=80=9CWe need to at least talk about stuff like that. Imagine our foo=
tprint.=E2=80=9D St. John=E2=80=99s coach <strong>Rick Pitino</strong> agre=
ed, telling Krzyzewski, =E2=80=9CI jumped on your bandwagon with the sugges=
tion you had about combining with the ACC because I=E2=80=99ve been trying =
to get them to start a super-league
basketball league.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>I floated the idea to Big East commiss=
ioner <strong>Val Ackerman</strong> on yesterday=E2=80=99s edition of the <=
em>Varsity</em> <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRn=
VDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWT3d3VnoteWdtakc1ZUhLUTJHVT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9=
wdWNrLm5ld3MvcG9kY2FzdF9lcGlzb2RlL2JpZy1lYXN0LWhvb3AtZHJlYW1zLTIvP3V0bV9jYW=
